## Ticket: Laptop Will Not Wake from Sleep

**Issue:**
User reported that their laptop would not wake from sleep. The screen remained black while the power indicator light was blinking.

**Root Cause:**
The system became unresponsive while in sleep/hibernation mode.

**Resolution:**
- Verified the symptoms indicated the laptop was stuck in sleep/hibernation.
- Performed a forced shutdown by holding the power button for approximately 10 seconds until the device powered off.
- Powered the laptop back on and confirmed it booted normally.
- Verified the display was restored and the user was able to access the system.

**Status:**
✅ Resolved – Laptop restarted successfully and returned to normal operation.
